## Part 5 — Finances (Internal)

### Burn Context

Roughly $10,000 was invested in Outside Inn music and art — Carson Thatcher as composer, Marwan Hasnaoui as animator, and a failed earlier engagement before Marwan was found. This was spent before the brand exercise in February 2026 clarified that Outside Inn is an atmosphere layer, not the brand itself. The pivot was right. The cost of the pivot was $10k and several months. The lesson is the build-before-validate pattern: building to the scale of the person he wants to be before validating the premise. The fix is one question that precedes every new infrastructure build — what is the cheapest way to test whether this works before making it beautiful?

